'''Create a code that takes a tuple and two integers as input. The function should return a new tuple
containing elements from the original tuple within the specified range of indices'''

tuple1=(45,785,412,3,56,854,2563)

input1=int(input("Input1: "))
input2=int(input("Input2: "))

new_tuple=tuple1[input1:input2]

print("New Tuple: ", new_tuple)
